cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language parsing using a grammar formalism.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach to parsing using answer set programming, which is a declarative programming paradigm often used in AI.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of the C&C supertagger, which is a machine learning tool for part-of-speech tagging.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper uses answer set programming as its main computational means.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with normalization and efficiency issues in parsing.
